summary:
• Capital Raising Structure: Combination of renounceable rights issue ($9m) and placement to new cornerstone investor Amari Metals ($6m min, $15m-$24m total raise).
  • Pricing: 3c per share.
  • Ownership Post-Raising: Amari to hold 51.0%.
  • Conditions: Shareholder approval required (meeting expected late August 2025). Cross-completion with new loan facility.
  • New Loan Facility: 3-year term, same pricing as current facility. Current facilities extended to 30 September 2025.
  • Timetable: Offer documentation expected early August 2025.

(Omitted: Director names, investor background, operational commentary as non-material to capital structure/trading decisions.)

Summary of ASX Announcement: Quarterly Update (Appendix 4C Equivalent)

Key Highlights

  • Combogesic IV (Maxigesic IV) launch in Canada begins this month, targeting opioid alternatives in pain management.
  • US licensing agreement with Hikma Pharmaceuticals extended: Restructured profit-sharing for Combogesic IV/Rapid; Hikma to oversee all US channels (excluding Alexso’s niche markets).
  • R&D progress:
  • Pre-IND filed for antibiotic eyedrop (targeting resistant infections); IND filing planned pre-year-end.
  • Pre-IND upcoming for Strawberry Birthmarks topical; IND for novel iron injection by year-end.
  • New formulation project added (targeting ~US$180M niche market).
  • Pediatric expansion: Maxigesic IV study for pediatric use planned to broaden market.
  • Commercial pipeline: Five out-licensing deals completed; more in negotiation.

Strategic Impact

  • Expands North American footprint (Canada launch, US partnership restructuring).
  • Advances high-potential R&D assets with near-term regulatory milestones.

No material financial data (e.g., cash balance) disclosed.

• Redemption of Crown Funding Securities:
  • 85,341,018 unquoted CIP1 equity securities redeemed at NZ$1.00 each (total NZD 85.3M).
  • 7,561,881 unquoted CIP1 warrants cancelled at nil consideration.
  • Repayment of NZD 85.3M unquoted CIP1 debt securities.
  • Impact on Capital Structure:
  • Redemption reduces outstanding CIP1 equity securities to 376,711,053 (18.5% reduction).
  • Warrants outstanding reduced to 9,903,147 (43.3% cancellation).
  • Reason: Dividends became payable on a portion of CIP1 equity securities, triggering redemption under pre-existing terms.

No material trading or valuation impact identified for listed securities (NZX:CNU).

• Dividend Details:
  • Final dividend: NZD 0.1325 per share (AUD 0.1229 equivalent).
  • Record date: 12/6/2025.
  • Ex-date: 11/6/2025.
  • Payment date: 2/7/2025.

  • Currency: NZD (withholding tax rate: 15%).

  • Dividend Reinvestment Plan (DRP):

  • Strike price: NZD 10.42983548 per share (2% discount applied).
  • Election deadline: 13/6/2025.

  • DRP issue date: 2/7/2025.

  • Key Update: Adjustment to previously announced DRP strike price (no change to dividend amount or dates).
